# Metagraph Rules for Windsurf / Cascade

This project is a metagraph — a structured knowledge and task graph.
Full rules are defined in CLAUDE.md. This file provides the same rules for Windsurf agents.

---

## Quick Reference

### Folders
- `context/goal/` — OKR goals (horizon: quarter/half-year/year), linked to tasks
- `context/personal/` — people (`variant: about`) or personalal reflections (`variant: reflection`); entire node is PRIVATE, never leak outside graph
- `context/decision/` — decision log tables per domain (health, career, finance…)
- `context/knowledge/` — reference knowledge with external source (file/google_doc/jira/figma/notion/url)
- `tasks/todo|in-progress|done|ongoing/` — task tickets (IDs: T1001, …)
- `processes/` — process protocols (IDs: P1001, …)
- `archived/` — soft-deleted entities (original IDs preserved)
- `templates/message|jira|task|process/` — reusable output blueprints (no IDs); referenced from processes and tasks via `used_by` wikilinks

### Before doing anything
1. Read `CLAUDE.md` for full rules.
2. Read `INDEX.md` for current graph state and ID counters.
3. Load relevant context nodes from `context_refs` in the task.

### ID assignment
- Read `INDEX.md`, increment the counter, write it back FIRST, then create the file.
- Never reuse or skip IDs.

### Task lifecycle (move the file, don't copy)
```
todo/ → in-progress/ → done/
                     → ongoing/  (recurring tasks stay here)
```

### Required frontmatter fields (all files)
```yaml
id, type, title, created, modified, status, assignee
```

### Required frontmatter fields (tasks only)
```yaml
priority: low | medium | high | critical
deadline: YYYY-MM-DD | null
creator: human | process:<P-ID> | task:<T-ID>
```

### Extra frontmatter fields by context subtype
```yaml
# goal:      horizon: Q2-2026 | H1-2026 | 2026 — task_refs: [T-IDs]
# decision:  domain: health | career | finance | product | technical | other
# knowledge: source_type: file|google_doc|jira|figma|notion|url|other — source_ref: <path/URL> — updated_at: YYYY-MM-DD
# personal:    (standard fields only — Private Notes section is PRIVATE)
```
Always update `modified` when editing.

### Archiving (never hard-delete)
- Always ask the user for reason/feedback before archiving.
- Move to `archived/<type>/`, append `## Archive Record` section.
- Update `INDEX.md` archived table.

### Links — always use wikilinks
- Reference any entity as `[[ID]]` or `[[ID|label]]` — in body text, `## Related`, tables, and frontmatter lists.
- Frontmatter example: `context_refs: ["[[C1001]]", "[[P1001]]"]`
- Never use plain IDs or filenames as references.

### Git — every agent action = one commit
- Check for `.git` on first run; if missing, `git init` and initial commit.
- Commit format: `<type>(<ID>): <short reason>` — e.g. `create(C1001): add Q2 goal node`
- Stage only files changed by the current action.
- Never push unless explicitly asked.

